    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="148"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/571: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 6, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>381. Embassy at Tokyo in telegram No. 231, December 6, 9 a.m.,<note n="96"
                        xml:id="d148fn96">Not printed.</note> reports “newspapers yesterday and
                    today have carried stories to the effect that the Japanese delegates to the
                    London Conference would make proposals in regard to the Four Power Treaty<note
                        n="97" xml:id="d148fn97">Signed at Washington December 13,. 1921, <ref
                            target="frus1922v01#pg_33">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1922, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 33</ref>.</note> and in regard to
                    fortifications in the Pacific. I took occasion to inquire at the Foreign Office
                    and was informed that there is no basis for these reports and that the Japanese
                    delegates are not authorized to introduce political subjects at London.”</p>
                <p>Please inform Naval Delegation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
